This Terminal Phase-out Management Phase was approved by the 56th Meeting of the Executive Committee of the Multilateral Fund (Ex Com) in November 2008, in Doha, Qatar. UNEP is the lead implementing agency and UNDP is the implementing partner agency while the Swaziland Environment Authority (SEA) National Ozone Unit (NOU) is the national partner. The project aims to:

•	Reinforce three existing training institutions, assisting them to put in place a "Refrigeration Technician" course sanctioned by a diploma, and enabling them to provide students and certified technicians who are members of the Refrigeration Technicians Association, with access to up-to-date information, tools and equipment;
•	Setting up an end user incentives scheme for the limited number of remaining commercial/industrial facilities (under the guidance of a National consultant, and on a first come first serve basis);
•	Strengthening one or two high profile end-use workshops provide incentives on a first come first serve to 500 vehicle owners.

